#   CODE-019: relocate `sha1hex` from `dog/WHIFF.h` to `dog/git/SHA1.h` (beside its sibling `sha1`)

`dog/WHIFF.h` is about packed index words (`wh64`/`wh128`) + SHA→hashlet
keys — but it ALSO defines `sha1hex` (the 40-ASCII-hex SHA-1 struct) and its
bin↔hex conversions, which WHIFF's own logic never uses. Its sibling, the binary
`sha1` struct + SHA-1 hashing, already lives in `dog/git/SHA1.h` (which even has
a 40-hex feed helper). `sha1hex` belongs there. TIGHT, behaviour-preserving move
+ include fixes — NOT an open cleanup. Method: [Issues].

##  Input

### Context
 -  Defined in `dog/WHIFF.h:151-196`: `sha1hex` struct + `sha1hexcp`, `sha1hexZ`
    (sort), `sha1hexFromSha1`, `sha1FromSha1hex`, `sha1hexeq`, `sha1hexSlice`,
    `sha1hexFromHex`, and the `#define X(M,n) M##sha1hex##n` Bx instantiation.
 -  WHIFF's `wh64`/`wh128` packing + `WHIFFHashlet*`/hex-key code does NOT reference
    `sha1hex` — it is pure colocation (WHIFF.h is header-only).
 -  Its sibling lives in `dog/git/SHA1.h`: the binary `sha1` struct (`:13`,
    "git SHA-1 type + hashing via sha1dc"), `sha1Z`, `sha1slice`, `SHA1Sum/Open/Feed/
    Close`, `SHA1u8sFeedHashlet`, and already a "feed all 40 ASCII hex chars" helper
    (`:78`). The right home for the 40-hex twin + its conversions.
 -  Reach: `sha1hex` is used by dog(3)/graf(9)/keeper(7)/sniff(7)/beagle(1) ≈ 27 sites,
    ZERO in `abc/` — a git-compat object-id type, correct at the `dog/git` layer.
 -  [CODE-016] (LANDED `0a43dec5`) already "centralize[d] sha1↔hex through
    `dog/git/SHA1.h`" — so that home is established; the `sha1hex` STRUCT + its methods
    just stayed behind in `WHIFF.h`. CODE-019 finishes that move; consistent direction.

### Goals
 -  Move the `sha1hex` block (struct, `sha1hexcp`, `sha1hexZ`, `sha1hexFromSha1`,
    `sha1FromSha1hex`, `sha1hexeq`, `sha1hexSlice`, `sha1hexFromHex`, the Bx `sha1hex`
    instantiation) from `dog/WHIFF.h` → `dog/git/SHA1.h`, placed beside `sha1`.
 -  WHIFF.h is left with `wh64`/`wh128` + `WHIFFHashlet*`/hex-key helpers only.
 -  Every former consumer still resolves `sha1hex`: files that pulled it via
    `dog/WHIFF.h` now `#include "dog/git/SHA1.h"` (keep both if a file needs both).

### Constraints
 -  PURE behaviour-preserving move — signatures/bodies BYTE-IDENTICAL, no rename. Only
    the home + `#include`s change. `dog/git/SHA1.h` must carry whatever `sha1hex` needs
    (HEX `HEXu8sFeedSome`/`DrainSome`, `u8sCopy`, `a_dup`) — it already includes the abc
    deps for `sha1`; add any missing. Mind include cycles (WHIFF.h must NOT now pull
    git/SHA1.h unless it already does).
 -  TIGHT + mechanical. The CODE board warns prior sweeps were BS — do exactly this move,
    nothing more. Full `ctest -j16 --timeout 10` green; build IS the correctness gate.

##  WIP

### Design decisions
 -  The move is the deliverable; `sha1FromSha1hex` (`sha1*`←`sha1hex const*`) and
    `sha1hexFromSha1` (`sha1hex*`←`sha1cp`) end up in the SAME file as `sha1`, removing a
    cross-header dependency rather than adding one.

